cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "cheb-spde: A Chebyshev exponential-integrator solver for stochastic PDEs on bounded domains"
abstract: "Fast and memory-efficient Python package for simulating parabolic stochastic PDEs on bounded intervals with time-dependent Dirichlet boundary data and either additive white or Ornstein-Uhlenbeck noise. Combines Chebyshev-collocation spatial discretization with a stochastic exponential-Euler time step whose linear dynamics are propagated exactly via Talbot-contour matrix phi-functions and whose stochastic convolution is sampled exactly in the operator eigenbasis."
authors:
